X: 180
T: Day of Wrath, O Day of Mourning
T: (SSAATTBB arrangement)
C: Words: Thomas of Celano, 13th Century. Translated by William J. Irons, 1848.
C: Music: 'Dies Irae (Dykes)' John Bacchus Dykes, 1861. Setting: "Hymns Ancient and Modern", 1869.
C: SSAATTBB arr. for 8-voice ensemble with lever harp.
C: copyright: public domain.
M: 4/4
L: 1/4
Q: 1/4=100
%%staves [(V1 V2) (V3 V4) (V5 V6) (V7 V8)]
V:1 name="Soprano I"  clef=treble
V:2 name="Soprano II" clef=treble
V:3 name="Alto I"     clef=treble
V:4 name="Alto II"    clef=treble
V:5 name="Tenor I"    clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:6 name="Tenor II"   clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:7 name="Baritone"   clef=bass
V:8 name="Bass I"     clef=bass
K: F
%
% ============================================================
% PHRASE 1 (bars 1–3): SSAA choir, TTBB silent
% Texture: 4-voice opening — antiphonal, soprano-led
% Chords: F | Dm | Gm | F | F/A | Dm | Bb | Gm | F | Dm
% ============================================================
%
[V:1] [Q:1/4=100] F3/2 E/ D E | F G A D | B B A D |
